# Financial Risk Intelligence Documentation Roadmap

## Purpose

This document translates the master guide into the documentation set needed to execute the project as an engineering program rather than as a loose study plan.

## Roadmap Analysis

The roadmap is strong, but it spans five different concerns that need explicit documentation ownership:

1. Product and governance
2. Data and fraud domain understanding
3. Model and graph intelligence development
4. Platform, deployment and operations
5. Analyst experience and portfolio packaging

The highest-risk execution gaps are not model selection. They are:

- unclear problem framing and success metrics
- undocumented data contracts and validation rules
- no traceability between business objectives and model outputs
- no architectural baseline for how graph, temporal and API layers fit together
- no operational documents for deployment, monitoring and drift response

## Documentation Strategy

Use three levels of documentation:

1. Foundation docs
   - define what is being built and why
2. Build docs
   - specify how each subsystem works
3. Run docs
   - define how the platform is deployed, monitored and operated

## Required Documentation Set

| Phase | Document | Purpose | Priority |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 0 | PRD | Establish scope, users, workflows, success metrics and constraints | Critical |
| 0 | Requirements Traceability Matrix | Tie each requirement to implementation and validation | Critical |
| 0 | Architecture Vision | Define system boundaries, layers, interfaces and deployment assumptions | Critical |
| 1 | Fraud Taxonomy | Standardize fraud typologies and investigation vocabulary | Critical |
| 1 | Dataset Assessment | Compare candidate datasets, fields, gaps and suitability | Critical |
| 1 | Entity Relationship Mapping | Normalize business entities and their relationships before graph construction | Critical |
| 2 | Architecture Diagram Pack | Capture context, container, data flow, sequence, deployment and ER views | Critical |
| 3 | Data Dictionary | Define schema, data types, null rules and business meaning | Critical |
| 3 | EDA Report | Document class imbalance, outliers, leakage risks and quality issues | Critical |
| 3 | Data Validation Specification | Define validation checks, thresholds, owners and failure handling | Critical |
| 4 | Feature Store Design | Describe offline and online feature contracts and lineage | Critical |
| 4 | Feature Documentation | Define each feature, window, formula and leakage controls | Critical |
| 5 | Model Development Plan | Define baselines, splits, metrics and experiment strategy | Critical |
| 5 | Evaluation Report | Compare model families and document tradeoffs | Critical |
| 5 | Feature Importance Report | Provide model interpretation for baseline models | High |
| 6 | Graph Schema Specification | Define nodes, edges, identifiers and graph construction rules | Critical |
| 6 | Graph Analytics Report | Document community detection, ring patterns and cluster findings | High |
| 7 | Embedding Pipeline Specification | Define node embedding generation, storage and reuse | Critical |
| 7 | Graph Feature Service Spec | Define graph-derived feature computation for training and inference | High |
| 7 | Performance Comparison Report | Compare classical, hybrid and graph ML systems | Critical |
| 8 | Temporal Feature Service Spec | Define rolling windows, drift signals and behaviour baselines | Critical |
| 8 | Drift Detection Engine Spec | Document rules, thresholds and action paths for behaviour change | High |
| 8 | Behaviour Analytics Dashboard Spec | Define analyst views for temporal monitoring | High |
| 9 | Explainability Service Spec | Define reason codes, SHAP outputs and explanation APIs | Critical |
| 9 | Risk Explanation Dashboard Spec | Define how analysts consume model explanations | High |
| 10 | MLOps Pipeline Spec | Document experiments, training orchestration and reproducibility | Critical |
| 10 | Model Lifecycle Documentation | Define promotion, rollback, approval and registry rules | Critical |
| 11 | API Specification | Define endpoints, request and response schemas, auth and SLAs | Critical |
| 11 | Deployment Guide | Document local, staging and production deployment steps | Critical |
| 12 | Monitoring Plan | Define data, feature, prediction and latency monitoring | Critical |
| 12 | Alerting Framework | Define thresholds, on-call actions and escalation paths | Critical |
| 13 | Dashboard Product Spec | Define dashboard personas, views and workflows | Critical |
| Final | Demo Narrative | Provide end-to-end story for reviewers and interviews | High |
| Final | Resume Project Entry | Distill project into resume-ready impact statements | Medium |
| Final | Interview Story Bank | Prepare technical, business and tradeoff narratives | Medium |

