## Definition Of Done For Project Documentation

A project document is complete when it:

- states owner, objective and scope
- defines assumptions and open questions
- identifies dependencies on datasets, models or services
- includes measurable acceptance criteria
- can be used directly by implementation or review work

## Next Authoring Priority

After the phase-0 documents, the next best investment is phase 1 domain documentation, especially the fraud taxonomy and dataset assessment, because they directly influence entity design, feature engineering and graph construction.
